text: Elizabethtown is a hamlet and census-designated place (CDP) in the town of Elizabethtown in Essex County, New York, United States. The population of the CDP was 746 at the 2020 census, out of a total town population of 1,203. Elizabethtown is the county seat of Essex County and the location of the town government. ==References== Category:Hamlets in New York (state) Category:County seats in New York (state) Category:Census-designated places in New York (state)
